"The Z with `subtract_min=True` is value of the function away from minimum. To interpret this as how many sigma: each line of the countour is n^2*up where n is number of sigma.\n\nhttp://wwwasdoc.web.cern.ch/wwwasdoc/minuit/node7.html\n\nThe automatic bound is from hesse which assumes parabolic error. If your profile is not exactly parabolic then ... just enlarge your bound.\n\nIf you are gettting weird image try using\n\n`contour(x,y,z, levels=[1,4,9])` for chi^2 and `contour(x,y,z, levels=[0.5,2,4.5])` for likelihood\n\n\nsee #57 \n"